#: src/migration.md:1
msgid "Migrating from older maturin versions"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide can help you upgrade code through breaking changes from one "
"maturin version to the next. For a detailed list of all changes, see the "
"[CHANGELOG](changelog.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:6
msgid "From 0.14.\\* to 0.15"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:8
msgid ""
"Build with `--no-default-features` by default when bootstrapping from sdist"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:10
msgid ""
"When bootstrapping maturin from sdist, maturin 0.15 will build with `--no-"
"default-features` by default, which means that for distro packaging, you "
"might want to set the environment variable `MATURIN_SETUP_ARGS=\"--features "
"full,rustls\"` to enable full features."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:13
msgid "Remove `[tool.maturin.sdist-include]`"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:15
msgid "Use `[tool.maturin.include]` option instead."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:17
msgid "Remove `[package.metadata.maturin]` from `Cargo.toml`"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:19
msgid ""
"Package metadata is now specified in `[tool.maturin]` section of `pyproject."
"toml` instead of `Cargo.toml`. Note that the replacement for `package."
"metadata.maturin.name` is `tool.maturin.module-name`."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:22
msgid "Require `uniffi-bindgen` CLI to building `uniffi` bindings"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:24
msgid ""
"maturin 0.15 requires `uniffi-bindgen` CLI to build `uniffi` bindings, you "
"can install it with `pip install uniffi-bindgen`."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:27
msgid "From 0.13.\\* to 0.14"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:29
msgid "Remove support for specifying python package metadata in `Cargo.toml`"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:31
msgid ""
"maturin 0.14 removed support for specifying python package metadata in "
"`Cargo.toml`, Python package metadata should be specified in the `project` "
"section of `pyproject.toml` instead as [PEP 621](https://peps.python.org/"
"pep-0621/) specifies."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:34
msgid "Deprecate `[tool.maturin.sdist-include]`"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:36
msgid ""
"maturin 0.14 added `[tool.maturin.include]` and `[tool.maturin.exclude]` to "
"replace `[tool.maturin.sdist-include]` which was sdist only, the new options "
"can be configured to apply to sdist and/or wheel."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:40
msgid "macOS deployment target version defaults what `rustc` supports"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:42
msgid ""
"If you don't set the `MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET` environment variable, "
"maturin 0.14 will use the default target version acquired from `rustc`, this "
"may cause build issue for projects that depend on C/C++ code, usually you "
"can fix it by setting a correct `MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET`, for example"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:48
msgid "10.9"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:51
msgid "Deprecate `python-source` option in `Cargo.toml`"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:53
msgid ""
"maturin 0.14 deprecated the `python-source` option in `Cargo.toml`, use "
"`[tool.maturin.python-source]` option in `pyproject.toml` instead."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:56
msgid "From 0.12.\\* to 0.13"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:58
msgid "Drop support for Python 3.6"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:60
msgid ""
"maturin 0.13 has dropped support for Python 3.6, to support Python 3.6 you "
"can use the old 0.12 versions."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:62
msgid "Removed `--cargo-extra-args` and `--rustc-extra-args`"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:64
msgid ""
"maturin 0.13 added most of the `cargo rustc` options so you can just use "
"them directly, for example `--cargo-extra-args=\"--no-default-features\"` "
"becomes `--no-default-features`."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:67
msgid ""
"To pass extra arguments to rustc, add them after `--`, for example use "
"`maturin build -- -Clink-arg=-s` instead of `--rustc-extra-args=\"-Clink-"
"arg=-s\"`."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:70
msgid "Source distributions are not built by default"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:72
msgid ""
"maturin 0.13 replaced `--no-sdist` with the new `--sdist` option in `maturin "
"build` command, source distributions are now only built when `--sdist` is "
"specified."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:75
msgid "Only build wheels for current Python interpreter in `PATH` by default"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:77
msgid ""
"maturin 0.13 no longer searches for Python interpreters by default and only "
"build wheels for the current Python interpreter (i.e. `python3`) in `PATH`."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:80
msgid "To enable the old behavior, use the new `--find-interpreter` option."
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:82
msgid "`--repository-url` only accepts full URL now"
msgstr ""

#: src/migration.md:84
msgid ""
"Previously `--repository-url` option in `maturin upload` and `maturin "
"publish` commands accepts both repository name and URL. maturin 0.13 changed "
"`--repository-url` to only accept full URL and added a new `--repository` "
"for the repository name. This new behavior matches `twine upload`."
msgstr ""
